ownedNfts.name: TIME: Into the Metaverse | August 15, 2022
ownedNfts.description:
TIMEPieces Genesis artist, Micah Johnson created the “Into the Metaverse” cover for the August 15, 2022 issue of TIME. 

Johnson, a former Major League baseball shortstop turned digital artist, rendered an image of a virtual portal featuring his character Aku, who Johnson considers the world’s first digital explorer.

“I wanted to present him in a way that he’s welcoming others into the world that gave him this incredible platform to begin his journey,” Johnson said of Aku on TIME’s cover.

Each NFT from this collection has the opportunity to receive an airdrop of Micah’s cover sketches that will be randomly airdropped to a very limited selection of minters. 

Your use of the TIMEPiece NFT is subject to the License available at https://time.com/privacy/timepieces_license_agreement.html. 

This limited license does not give you the right to modify the Artwork (including, as applicable, any digital TIME issue) in any way or to use the Artwork separately from the associated TIMEPiece NFT.

ownedNfts.name: Hopium
ownedNfts.description:
Memiotic Table of Elements

The Memiotic Table of Crypto Elements is an ongoing secret experiment conducted deep within the underground 6529 Meme Lab basement floor 69. The meme lab scientists are are probing the fundamental structure of the crypto universe. They use the world's largest and most complex scientific instruments to study the basic constituents of memetic matter to extract and catalog the fundamental crypto particles for further research.

The complex process involving a high-energy memetic particle accelerator and an advanced chemistry lab supported by various quantum computers and AI data analysis tools to extract both common and rare elements -, and prepare them for shipment to labs around the world for further research. 

The discovery of Hopium was a major milestone in crypto chemistry and crypto particle physics, confirming a key prediction of the existence of the alluding element and providing new insights into the fundamental nature of matter in the crypto universe. It required the collaboration of thousands of scientists and engineers from around the world, and it demonstrated the power of advanced scientific instruments and the importance of international decentralized scientific cooperation.

ownedNfts.name: Rugium
ownedNfts.description:
Memiotic Table of Elements

The Memiotic Table of Crypto Elements is an ongoing secret experiment conducted deep within the underground 6529 meme lab basement floor 69. The meme lab scientists are are probing the fundamental structure of the crypto universe. They use the world's largest and most complex scientific instruments to study the basic constituents of memetic matter to extract and catalog the fundamental crypto particles for further research.

Rugium is an element that has an atomic number of 8 and is represented by the symbol Rg on the memiotic table of crypto elements. It is a colorless, odorless, tasteless, and extremly-toxic gas that is the second most common element in the crypto universe, after Hopium.

The subatomic structure of Rugium consists of a nucleus composed of 8 protons and 8 neutrons, surrounded by 8 electrons. This special solid octagon structure allows it to bond with various NFT, crypto and DeFi project creating havoc and disintegration of all elements around it.

openSeaMetadata.description:
Impermanence is the nature of our world. While all of existence is in perpetual flux, the only constant is this moment. We wake each day to a breathing, living reality. This is why I focus on living in the present. There is nothing more precious than now. The one immutable quality of existence is perpetual change. Be with it always.

This piece is a real time geo-location specific NFT, the first of its kind to display your personalized local weather conditions. Watch each day as conditions change from cold to warm, night to day, snow storm, rain clouds, fog banks and many others. There are even secret hidden conditions that only the most patient observers will be able to spot when conditions are just right. In partnership with Transient Labs, we hope you enjoy the magic of Impermanence.

Humans are characterized by a desire to form communities around ideas, symbols, and artifacts that satisfy our overlapping interpretations of beauty. Tiles are a celebration of what gives meaning to those communities: the individual.

There is one Tile generated for every possible ETH wallet address—each representing a unique identity in the decentralized ecosystem that makes projects like this possible.

Mathematically, all Tiles are equally rare. They are all fashioned from the same assortment of simple shapes and colors, but each in a unique way. In that sense, Tiles are a bit like us.

Owning a Tile is an invitation to participate in the TileDAO, which receives all revenue from the Tiles primary sale. Because the supply is virtually infinite, funding for the DAO may continue indefinitely—as long as Tiles are sold.

Mathematically, all Tiles are equally rare. They are all fashioned from the same assortment of simple shapes and colors, but each in a unique way. In that sense, Tiles are a bit like us.

Owning a Tile is an invitation to participate in the TileDAO, which receives all revenue from the Tiles primary sale. Because the supply is virtually infinite, funding for the DAO may continue indefinitely—as long as Tiles are sold.

[Curio Cards](https://curio.cards) are the First art show NFTs on Ethereum, launched May 9, 2017 and pre-dating CryptoPunks. Featuring 30 unique series of cards from seven different artists, Curio Cards is referenced in the ERC-721 NFT Standard and pioneered features later adopted in the ERC-1155 NFT Standard. Check out the [Curio Docs](https://docs.curio.cards) and Join the [Curio Discord](https://discord.curio.cards) to learn more.

Given their age, Curio Cards are wrapped to work on newer platforms like OpenSea. If you purchased cards directly from the original contracts before March 2021, you can wrap them [here](https://wrap.curio.cards). Otherwise, you don't need to do anything. All cards on OpenSea are already wrapped and don't need to be unwrapped to collect.

The 1% artist royalty goes entirely to the original Curio Cards Artists.

openSeaMetadata.collectionName: Winds of Yawanawa by Yawanawa and Refik Anadol
openSeaMetadata.description:
A first-of-its-kind space of co-creation between the Brazilian Indigenous Yawanawa community and media artist Refik Anadol.

Launching this historical collaboration, the Yawanawa community and Refik Anadol Studio have co-authored the Genesis collection 'Winds of Yawanawa'. The collection of 1000 unique Data Paintings brings the nuances of Yawanawa art to the digital world with the aim of preserving the community’s rich culture.

First and only official collaborative wallet of Refik Anadol, with Instituto Nixiwaka; representing the Yawanawa communities of Aldeia Sagrada and Nova Esperança.

ownedNfts.name: Winds of Yawanawa #785 by Yawanawa and Refik Anadol
ownedNfts.description:
Winds of Yawanawa is a collection of 1000 unique Data Paintings that harness weather data from the tribe’s village in the Amazon rainforest including wind speed, gusts, direction and temperature. This data then merges with the works of young Yawanawa artists, resulting in a mesmerizing play of traditional shapes and colors of data pigmentation.

The Winds of Yawanawa collection will bring the nuances of Yawanawa art to the digital world with the aim of preserving their rich culture.

NFT Data Paintings
Format: MP4 | 60 second loop

Each NFT comes with an archival museum quality physical print (44x22 inches) signed by Chief Nixiwaka Yawanawa & Refik Anadol

openSeaMetadata.description: Rare Pepes is a historic NFT collection of 1,774 unique cards with varying designs and rarities that were minted from 2016 to 2018. The collection was created using the Counterparty protocol on the Bitcoin blockchain and is the first decentralized community art project in the history of NFTs. More than 300 artists submitted cards that were approved by the Rare Pepe Scientists, who curated the completion of 36 series of 50 cards each (Series 36 ended with 24 cards). This collection is curated by Emblem Vault.
